1.Merges the training and the test sets to create one data set.
2.Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement.
3.Uses descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set.
4.Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names.
5.Creates a second, independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.

The object of the activity_label read from activity_labels.TXT
The object of the features read from features.txt
The object of the subject_train read from subject_train.txt
The object of the X_train read from X_train.txt
The object of the Y_train read from Y_train.txt
The object of the subject_test read from subject_test.txt
The object of the X_test read from X_test.txt
The object of the Y_test read from Y_test.txt

I Used function factor() cbind() grep() aggregate()







